address.city: Cheyenne, WY to Ft. Carson, CO

title: Laramie Enduro 2010
description: Situated in the Laramie Range of Southeastern Wyoming, the course is a challenging 72.5 miles climbing over 8,600 vertical feet, all above 7,500 feet elevation. The route is a fast and extremely fun loop, covering no ground twice, except the initial/final 0.8 miles. It includes virtually every kind of trail and surface a mountain biker is likely to encounter in the Rockies, from wildlife trails to single track to dirt roads. This event is not for the casual or beginner rider.
course: 72.5 miles, the initial/final 0.8 miles is repeated in opposite directions. We are not allowed to post the map on the website per USFS requirement
registration: Maximum racer limit 500 participants; $65 per rider before May 1, 2010; $80 per rider after April 30, 2010; On-line registration link posted on website; Packet pick-up on Friday July 30, 3-8 PM at Fine Edge Cycle & Sports (refer to website for contact information); Absolutely, NO RACE DAY REGISTRATION OR Packet Pick-up
notes: Race proceeds benefit the Albany County Chapter of the American Red Cross of Wyoming, Medicine Bow Mountain Bike Patrol, and other local and regional non-profit organizations. Laramie Enduro is a 501(C)3 Non-Profit Organization. http://www.LarmieEnduro.org.
directions: From Laramie: Travel approximately 9.5 miles east (of the Grand Ave. Exit) on I-80. Take the Summit Rest Area Exit (Exit 323), turn left (towards the rest area) and continue straight on USFS Road 705 (Blair-Wallis Road) past the Summit Rest Area. Follow the Blair-Wallis Road for approximately 0.5 miles and look for the parking signs (race parking will be on the left along Road 705F-No Parking along Road 705. Proceed another 0.3 miles down Road 705 to the Hidden Valley Picnic Area - follow signs to the parking & start areas. From Cheyenne: Travel approximately 39 miles west on I-80 take the Summit Rest Area Exit (Exit 323) turn right (towards the rest area) and continue straight on USFS Road 705 – from that point follow directions listed above.

title: Stone Temple 8
description: This race will be run on the new IMBA designed single track trails at Wyoming’s Curt Gowdy State Park. Racers will compete for eight hours on an approximately 8.5 mile figure-8 loop, in teams and as individuals. The start/finish is will be located at the Aspen Grove Trailhead Parking Area.
course: Trail Map Info: http://wyoparks.state.wy.us/Parks/CurtGowdy/index.asp; From Aspen Grove Trailhead: LeMans Start approx. 200 yard run to parked bikes - (first lap only) - Head west on the entrance road, proceeding up two-track west of the corrals for 1.1 miles. All subsequent laps will proceed up the single track Equestrian Trail directly west of the corrals (approximately 0.9 miles). Proceed onto Albert’s Alley Trail and continue on the trail for its\' entire length. Cross bridge and turn right onto Crow Creek Trail. Proceed 0.15 mile and turn left through fence gate onto the Mo Rocka Trail. Continue on Mo Rocka for 1 mile, turning left onto Sammie’s Slide Trail and continue another 0.25 mile to intersection with Crow Creek Trail. Turn left and continue 0.2 miles to a bridge, cross the bridge, and then proceed right onto the Pinball Trail. Ride the entire length of Pinball (0.5 mile) to the junction with the Stone Temple Circuit. Bear left and continue 2.7 miles to junction with the Igneoramus Trail. Turn left and proceed along Igneoramus for 0.25 miles to the upper junction with the Rock and Roller Trail. Turn left again and ride entire length of Rock and Roller (0.9 mile) to the lower junction with the Igneoramus Trail. Turn left and continue 0.35 miles down to junction with the Stone Temple Circuit Trail. Turn left and return to the Aspen Grove Trailhead (0.5 mile).
registration: $45 per solo rider before September 15, 2010; $60 per solo rider after September 15, 2010; $30 per team rider before September 15, 2010; $50 per team rider after September 15, 2010; On-line registration link and info listed on website; Packet Pick-up at race start/finish area (Curt Gowdy State Park) 7:30-8:50 AM Day of race registration at race start/finish area (Curt Gowdy State Park) 7:30-8:50 AM (cash or check only), if race limit (99 riders) not exceeded.
notes: Solo Riders: M&F under 40 and 40+ 2 and/or 3 Person Teams: Male, Female, Coed 3 Person Junior Teams: 13-18 The promoter reserves the right to revise the age categories should rider distribution be significantly unequal. The promoter reserves the right to combine age categories should one age category contain less than 10 riders. See website for list of rules, etc.
directions: Directions to Curt Gowdy State Park: From Cheyenne, WY take I-25 to exit 10 and travel 25 miles west on Highway 210, Happy Jack Road. From Laramie take I-80 east to exit 323 and travel east 14 miles on Highway 210. Follow signs at the park entrance on south side of Highway 210.
